messages.msgSnippet: Yep!  Fort Clinch rocks.  We got on a fairly regular basis just to do little hikes or walk out on the pier on a nice day. Fort Clinch is so many different
messages.messageBody:
Yep! Fort Clinch rocks. We got on a fairly regular basis just to do little hikes or walk out on the pier on a nice day.

Fort Clinch is so many different things. History, science, marine biology.

We were out walking the pier about 2 months ago and this guy had what looked like a mini hammerhead, except the head didn't look quite right. It was then that I learned of the "Bonnet Head Shark"...The kids thought it was pretty amazing.

Holly

messages.messageBody:
We're just north of Jax in Fernandina Beach.

(Maybe if I can round up a few more North Floridians, we can plan an outing to the theater.) I know my kids love to go to that one. It's so fancy in there. Yet it's inviting. Not like "too fancy to get comfy".

Holly

whole family drove over from Gainesville for the day. It was the fanciest

experience.

So you're living in Jax, now? I'm a couple of hours to your west, in
the currently-crowded-with-legislators city. :) JJ
